What you need to know:  Wayne Fernandes, who was admitted at the Aga Khan Hospital after an accident in the Kajiado Rally, has been discharged.“All is okay for now. I am getting a lot better after I was discharged from the hospital last Monday night. I am supposed to go back in a fortnight’s time to check on my progress. I am supposed to start physiotherapy soon. I have a minor pain while I am standing or sitting.  But managing with pain killers,” Fernandes told Nation Sport.